article.headline: Wofford 73, Davidson 51
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Noah Dahlman scored 19 points to lead Wofford to a 73-51 victory over Davidson to extend the Terriers' winning streak to seven consecutive games. Thirteen players scored and 15 played for Wofford (20-8, 12-3 Southern Conference), which has won 16 of its past 18 games and is in second behind the College of Charleston (18-9, 13-3) in the South Division. It is Wofford's first 20-win season since moving to Division I and its first since 1993-94. Davidson (13-13, 8-6) cut Wofford's lead to 44-31 on Jake Cohen's 3 with 15:44 left, but Terry Martin scored the next four points to spark a 16-5 run and give the Terriers a 60-36 lead with 6:32 to play. Jamar Diggs added 10 points for Wofford, which shot 52.2 percent in the first half (12-for-23) for a 38-22 halftime lead. Cohen scored 17, going 10-for-10 from the line, and J.P. Kuhlman added 13 points for Davidson.
